Notes. Specimens with tomentous markings (previously considered to be
E . leucopyge
), are more common in the northern part of its range but are also found elsewhere.

Geographic Distribution. Known from northern Mexico south through Honduras ( Fig. 4f ). Morón et al . (1997) is the only record known from Chihuahua , Mexico (recorded as
E . leucopyge
). Three specimens with label data for Austin, TX, USA are considered suspect as the species probably does not occur in that area. The northernmost distribution for the species is northeastern Mexico (Linares, Nuevo León , which is 627 km south of Austin).

